Tsasha is a boom professor, very SEXY and smart!

She was very enthusiastic about course material.  The tests were extremely vague yet the text and lectures were extremely detailed so you still had to study everything, which was a bit much.  But the tests were easy nonetheless.

Tests are out of a small total and a lot of short answers, very few multiple choice. Text bk. was jam-packed with info & studies (hard to take out main pts) = major info overload. Makes class interesting, is enthusiastic (not boring). If you can handle mostly short answers on the test for a 2nd yr. course, then this class is for you.
